            {"type": "paragraph", "content": "Dtype matters more than beginners expect. Integer tensors are fine for indexes or labels, but many training computations need floating point tensors because gradients and parameter updates involve decimal values. If a result looks strange, checking `x.dtype` is often worthwhile."},
