            {"type": "paragraph", "content": "A dimension is just an axis. For a matrix of shape `(2, 3)`, dimension 0 points across rows and dimension 1 points across columns. That is why summing with `dim=0` collapses rows and gives one value per column, while `dim=1` collapses columns and gives one value per row."},
