            {"type": "math", "title": "Chain Rule Result", "content": "dz/dx = sec²(log(u)) · (1/u) · (3x²y³ + y + y²)\ndz/dy = sec²(log(u)) · (1/u) · (3x³y² + x + 2yx)\n\nu = x³y³ + xy + y²x"},
            {"type": "paragraph", "content": "That is exactly the style of work autograd is automating. It does not use magic. It applies the chain rule through the computation graph. Each node knows how to propagate gradients to its parents. PyTorch multiplies and accumulates those local gradient contributions for you."},
