            {"type": "paragraph", "content": "Broadcasting is the rule that allows PyTorch to combine different shapes when they are compatible. For example, adding a bias vector of shape `(3,)` to a matrix of shape `(2, 3)` works because PyTorch conceptually copies that bias across both rows."},
